# container commands expalantion

For pushing images 
================

	1. Docker Tag:- it will tag ur image with ur dockerhub username  

docker tag <image-name>   <username/image-name>

	2. Docker login :- 

docker login -u muralisocial123

	3. Docker push:- to pushing the into docker registry from ur host machine 

docker push  <tagged image only>


Container lifecycle 
===============

Docker create:- it will create only container 
Docker run :- it will pull the image, it will create the container and it will start the container.
Docker ps:- it will list only running containers
Docker ps -a: it will list all containers in the server
Docker start: it will start the container
Docker stop:- it will stop the container
Docker restart :- it will restart the container
Docker stats:- it will show you container cpu, memory usage
Docker logs:- it will give container or app logs
Docker inspect:- it will give container ip add and all details of container
Docker pause: it will pause only container process not the app
Docker unpause:it will unpause the container process 
Docker rm:- it will remove only stopped containers
Docker rm -f :- it will delete running containers
Docker rmi :- it will delete only unused images
Docker rmi -f :- it will delete unsed images
Docker rmi $(docker images -q): - to delete all images at time
docker rm $(docker ps -aq): it will delete all stopped containers
Yashwardhan Kashyap (Unverified)


docker rm -f  $(docker ps -aq): it will delete all stopped n running containers.
